B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                              FY 2027    FY 2027      FY 2027
                                                                                                                        FY 2025   FY 2026     Base       OOC          Total
-SABER will continue the employment of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning methods and techniques in
FY2026.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
-SABER will begin the design and development of SABER capabilities in the Combat Systems and Navigation
afloat functional domains. This will include stand up of a new Boundary Defense & Situational Awareness
Solution (BD&SAS) CS/NAV Mid-Tier Acquisition program, design of new two-rack solution to minimize overall
footprint and simplify hardware solution, initiation of required shipboard installation packages, and publication of
a consolidated fielding plan.
-SABER will begin dedicated support to Missile Defense Agency (MDA) Guam to develop and prototype the first
SABER shore-side system.
-As part of direction to implement integrated Defensive Cyber Operations capability under the Information
System Capability Development Document (IS-CDD), SABER will begin to prototype an integrated fielding pilot
with SHARKCAGE to demonstrate movement of data off ship to shore DCO operations centers. The integrated
fielding pilot will inform the consolidated fielding plan for additional stem-to-stern coverage.
-SABER will implement ship/strike group grooms, with focus on near term deployers, to maintain and upgrade
current HM&E installations.
-SABER will continue research, development, testing, and evaluation necessary to support upcoming ship
installs to additional platforms and pace the emerging Cyber threat. SABER will support upgraded capabilities for
the 30 currently fielded systems.
-SABER will continue development of automation technologies for software qualification as well as start the
employment of those automation technologies to accelerate capability delivery.
-SABER will continue developments to enumeration technology tools, additional shipboard controllers, and
shipboard enumeration events as part of pre-deployment cyber upgrade events in support of U.S. Navy's
Pinnacle 27 objectives.
-SABER will continue investigation of technologies to handle increased bandwidth in support of maturing enclave
requirements.
-SABER will continue to mature advanced capabilities to support developing cyber threat requirements including
activities related to updating the program's threat model.
-SABER will continue the development employment of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning methods and
techniques to increase system usability for fleet operators.
