 SHARKCAGE: SHARKCAGE is transitioning from Rapid Deployment Capability (RDC) to Program of Record and will leverage COTS software and hardware configured
 to existing Navy networks and enclaves to detect, analyze, and assess cyber threats. SHARKCAGE will provide Navy Cyber Defense Operations Command (NCDOC),
 Navy Information Operations Centers (NIOC), Fleet Cyber Command/Commander Tenth Fleet (FCC/C10F), Cyber Protection Teams (CPT), and other CND deployers
 with a global Defensive Cyberspace Operations (DCO) enclave to monitor the Naval Networking Environment (NNE) and maritime Navy networks, including Navy
 ashore sites and afloat platforms conducting Ballistic Missile Defense (BMD) and other mission requirements (details held at a higher classification).

 Navy Cyber Situational Awareness (NCSA): NCSA is a Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP) program that integrates Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) and
 Government Off-The-Shelf (GOTS) products to provide visualization of Navy networks and enclaves for mission threat analysis and assessment. The program entered
 Planning Phase on December 2, 2020, and Execution Phase on November 8, 2021, following the October 7, 2021 Acquisition Decision Memorandum (ADM). NCSA
 implements an iterative, agile software enhancement process delivering annual capability releases to address evolving cyber Situational Awareness (SA) capabilities
 required by fleet warfighters. These government-led agile enhancements are documented and managed through a structured requirements governance board process.
 The program empowers warfighters with real-time understanding of network status and cyber threat impacts by: Enabling delivery of universal Cyber Common
 Operational Pictures (Cyber COP); Leveraging the Navy's Big Data Platform (BDP) to correlate data across the Joint Cyber Warfare Architecture (JCWA); Supporting
 data visualization through solutions such as NCCD and RAVEN. Requirements originated from the 2016 Maritime Cyber Situational Awareness (MCSA) Concept of
 Operations (CONOPS) and are further specified in the NCSA Capability Needs Statement (CNS) approved on October 3, 2021. Priorities for each Capability Release
 (CR) are updated annually by the PMW 130 Cyber SA Capabilities Advisory Board (CAB) based on the CNS and annual Value Assessment (VA) governed by the User
 Agreement (UA). CR priorities receive final approval from the Navy Cybersecurity Capabilities Steering Group (CCSG).




