Description: Joint Targeting Intelligence Modernization (JTIM) provides funding for the development of Joint Targeting Toolbox-
Capabilities Package (JTT-CP) and WARPATH tools. JTT is the current capability providing the joint targeting community
enterprise with Intermediate Target Development (ITD), Advanced Target Development (ATD), Target List Management (TLM),
and Target Folder Development capabilities. It also supports pairity and installation on Coalition-Partner networks and Foreign
Military Sales (FMS).

The JTT program provides the current (legacy) functions until the integrated JTIM capabilities are fielded and integrated with
Machine-Assisted Rapid-Repository System (MARS).

Development and integration of Target List Management functions, Enterprise Target Element/Object standards, and Target
Development Workflows are continuing from the JTT program to WARPATH to keep pace with the JTIM Integrated Master
Schedule (IMS). Funding for WARPATH comes from the original JTT budget, which is managed at ACC.

Full funding will allow both programs to develop and integrate field capabilities in FY26, and will merge into one enterprise
program providing capabilities to the Joint Targeting Enterprise along with MARS development.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continued development and integration of JTTv5 (JTT-CP) and v6 capabilities into WARPATH Target List Management capability.

USAF requested and Congress reprogrammed erroneous FY26 funds (7.693M) from AF JWICS/AF SCI Enterprise
(PE:0305249F) back to CAIS (PE:0207431F). Additionally, USAF has reprogrammed these funds back into CAIS in the out-years
FY27+in order to maintain continued unit-level and targeting enterprise development.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continued integration and development of JTTv6.

In FY27 WARPATH development till move to the US Navy for continued development dedicated to Target List Management and
Target Element Workflow capabilities.
