B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                               FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027

This is designed to accelerate kill chains to-up scale dynamic execution, increase the scope (aka the number of simultaneous
targets), develop Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures (TTPs) for targeting in the Agile Combat Environment (ACE), and
enhanced target mensuration development to improve speed and capacity for target location.

Funds dynamic Find-Fix-Target-Track-Engage-Assess (F2T2EA) S2S intelligence and advanced training on cloud-based
application to shorten LRKC with automated/AI-enabled sensing-grid and targeting/applications. Analyzes, visualizes, and shares
national, tactical, and open source intelligence to close the capability gap against adversary's truncated kill-chains.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue Kill Chain Acceleration/Automation efforts between the Intelligence Unit-Level and greater Air and Joint Forces
community.

Enhance F2T2EA S2S intelligence systems of record/programs of primacy focusing on data standardization, Object/Element
normalization, and systems integration. Additionally, supports development for training on applications to shorten and automate
long range kill chains in accordance with current operations and Joint Warfighting Concepts 3.0.

This includes intelligence Unit-level-to-National integration of: Turbo (Disposition-of-Forces Object/Elements); Cognos
(Algorithmic/AI data visualization and system insight analysis); Snapglass (Common Intelligence/Operating Picture and
