Description: STITCHES is a government-owned, open-source integration framework built by the DoW to accelerate mission
system interoperability. It connects diverse architectures, regardless of scale, without relying on rigid standards, enabling rapid
adaptation in dynamic operational environments. Proven across multiple platforms, STITCHES empowers programs to integrate
faster, smarter, and with greater resilience.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Scope, lead, and deploy STITCHES integrations and train DoW personnel. Lead continual development for STITCHES Platform
and new certification processes at AFLCMC/HNJJ direction.

- Improve STITCHES verification, validation, and testing capabilities through automation, Graphical User Interface development,
and streamline the developmental process for STITCHES toolchain and projects.

- Continue deploying STITCHES toolchain and repository into web-based infrastructure for unclassified/classified information
systems. Deploy secure cloud and non-cloud structures and NDAA 2021 Section 804 repositories within FENCES environment.
Maintain CUI and classified cloud and stand-alone/edge structure ATOs.

- Develop EW/EMSO capabilities through creation novel kill chains and EA/ES/EP involving previously incompatible weapon
systems, Mission Design Series, sensor, and command, control, and communication systems. The development of advanced EW
capability projects through collaboration of all military services in cooperation with multiple MAJCOMs to support multiple AORs
such as United States Indo-Pacific Command and European Command. STITCHES will focus on traditional EW/EMSO problem
sets and new gaps in air, maritime, space, and cyberspace domains.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Scope, lead, and deploy STITCHES integrations and train DoW personnel. Lead continual development for STITCHES Platform
and new certification processes.

- Execution of testing, training, and integration efforts as directed by the MAJCOM requirements working group.

