streamlined transportation and financial data and processes, supporting the Joint Deployment and Distribution Enterprise (JDDE). Services and DoD agencies will
have a system to automate the linkage between transportation action tasks and transportation business related tasks across the full spectrum of financial activity, from
obligations through general ledger accounting. It will also close all major gaps that prevent auditability within the transportation spend across DoD and achieve significant
gains in two of the focus areas of the Department of Defense's Data Strategy: Senior Leader Decision Support and Business Analytics. Through the JTMS's ability to
seamlessly integrate financial data and information with transportation operations in the joint domain, it will give JDDE users the ability to see to the transactional level in
a resilient transportation network while reducing duplicate capabilities.

 This requirement supports performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

