D. Acquisition Strategy
The RQ-4 program's acquisition strategy is focused on supporting the existing RQ-4 Block 40 fleet and maintaining its Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance
(ISR) capability until divestment. Northrop Grumman Corporation serves as the prime contractor, responsible for delivering sustainment and support services. The
program utilizes a suite of contract vehicles, primarily Indefinite Delivery, Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) contracts, to cover activities including sustainment, retrofit, fielding,
and contract closeout.




