Title: A/MH-6M Block R Upgrade, Program Number 828                                                                          3.648   2.977            3.091      -           3.091
Description: The A/MH-6 aircraft is the USSOCOM’s only urban attack and assault platform and provides
reconnaissance, close air support (CAS), precision strike, infiltration (infil), exfiltration (exfil), and resupply
of SOF teams in hostile, denied, and politically sensitive areas. This specialized aircraft must be capable of
worldwide rapid deployment and operations in contested or anti-access/area denial (A2/AD) environments in
support of Multi-Domain Operations (MDO). The A/MH-6 allows the Joint Force to be more agile and responsive
to combat missions, Irregular Warfare and Military Operations Other than War (MOOTW). This program funds
the development and testing of SO-p equipment and modifications for the A/MH-6. It will include software
development and testing to integrate new capability, development and qualification of new hardware, and test
and evaluation of new weapons, sensors, communications systems, or aircraft modifications that increase
system performance.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue software updates to incorporate communications data upgrades and crypto modernization for
enhanced situational awareness as well as additional software applications. Begin improved main rotor

