D. Acquisition Strategy
Provide additional SATCOM capacity and enterprise resiliency through integration and teaming with commercial, international and other US Government partners.
Activities include studies, demonstrations, and coordination with industry and with government organizations including the U.S. Space Force, U.S. Army, U.S. Air Force
Research Laboratory, Space Warfighting Analysis Center, U.S. Space Force Commercial Satellite Communications Office, and the Defense Information Systems
Agency. A Firm Fixed-Price contract was awarded to Astranis on 27 September 2023 to evaluate PTW SATCOM applications for Geosynchronous Earth Orbit small
satellites within the PTES architecture. Massachusetts Institute of Technology/Lincoln Labs to conduct a demonstration of PTW operations over mPOWER commercial
MEO satellites, the first allied hybrid government/commercial SATCOM solution. For the acquisition/integration of PTES with the mPOWER constellation, PTES procured
mPOWER teleports via the Commercial Satellite Communications Office (CSCO's) contract with the NATO Support and Procurement Agency, which funds mPOWER
bandwidth capacity in COMSATCOM PE 1206445SF, Project 650140. The contractual strategy to implement PTW over Commercial constellations will be informed by
the execution of the PTW over WGS effort.




