Description: The C-5 HAGAR program is a comprehensive effort to ensure appropriate HAGAR Line Replaceable Units
(LRU) are developed, integrated, and installed on the C-5M allowing aircraft operation in accordance with civil airspace access
mandates for both US National Airspace System (NAS) and international civil airspace. The C-5M HAGAR program will address
obsolescence issues with outdated LRUs by updating technology and mitigate the obsolescence of the current air data system,
mission computers, and the associated aircraft Operational Flight Program coding practices.

