In FY 2027, PE 0401134F, LAIRCM, Project 67A037, Latent Capability Development efforts transferred to PE 0401334F, Large Aircraft Survivability Systems (LASS),
project 67A038, Active Defense Sensor to focus on the development of an upward looking system to ensure aircraft survivability.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Latent Capability Development (LCD) develops the Large Aircraft Infrared Countermeasures (LAIRCM) system's ability to detect and defeat a distinct new category
of lethal threats and includes updates to the latest modeling and simulation threat models. It provides all support required to update the LAIRCM system hardware,
firmware, and software.

 Development begins at the AFRL Dynamic Infrared Missile Evaluation (DIME) Lab with support testing of code at the Guided Weapons Evaluation Facility (GWEF)
 before finally transitioning to Northrop Grumman Corporation (NGC) for inclusion into the LAIRCM software baseline. The LAIRCM system is an evolutionary acquisition
 program that provides significantly improved defensive systems capability for aircraft to counter the man-portable air-defense systems (MANPADS) missile threat. The
 system is installed on 54 aircraft variants and over 1200 aircraft.

 In FY 2027, LCD efforts transferred to PE 0401334F, Large Aircraft Survivability Systems (LASS), Project 67A038, Advanced Sensors, as the Advanced Capability
 Development (ACD) major thrust.

 Program support cost efforts consist of, but are not limited to, contract services and government costs.

 This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
 addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

