A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Project 674567, Modeling & Simulation Foundations, develops and supports a software tool named Air, Space and Cyberspace Collaborative Environment - Information
Operations Suite (ACE-IOS). ACE-IOS is used during major theater exercises to provide realistic intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR), electronic warfare
(EW), information operations (IO), and cyber effects simulation. ACE-IOS is part of the cyber live-virtual-constructive (LVC) environments for use during Joint training of
offensive and defensive ISR/cyber capabilities for the USAF, DoW, select coalition, and national agencies. ACE-IOS is also used at Air Force and Joint ISR operational
training, conducted by the AF simulation centers worldwide. Warfighters train using ACE-IOS models and simulations with specific extensions in support of the United
States Air Force (USAF) ISR schoolhouse.

 Robust ACE-IOS modernization is imperative to ensure that air, space, and cyberspace training and mission rehearsal activities can provide warfighters with realistic,
 interoperable, and readily available tools, data, and services. Planned ACE-IOS enhancements support of the users at mod-sim centers for multi domain capability and
 the USAF ISR schoolhouse. Specific cyber effects software extensions are required for warfighter training and exercising of tactical cyber mission forces (CMF).

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: Air, Space and Cyberspace Constructive Environment - Information Operations Suite (ACE-IOS)                                           8.993            17.291      11.334
Description: Provides the authoritative representation of the USAF ACE-IOS program. ACE-IOS is comprised of models that
support training and mission rehearsal for the USAF, Joint Task Force commanders, and Combatant Commander battle staffs
during Joint and service exercises and experimentations. Also supports shared ACE-IOS development in support of the USAF ISR
schoolhouse and Modeling and Simulation (M&S) centers.

FY 2026 Plans:
Delivered ACE-IOS version & deploy operational software modifications
- Started new ACE-IOS agile development providing modernized model and simulation updates for C5ISR training
- Developed and tested cross domain solution to connect to JWICS, Coalition, and SIPR domains for integrated AF CCMD training
- Updated tool sets based on operational needs to deliver realistic training in support of Joint/Combined Forces Air Component
Commander (JFACC/CFACC) operations
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will deliver continued annual ACE-IOS version & deploy operational software modifications to include fully containerized ACE-
IOS suite

