Note
In FY 2026, Program Element (PE) 0804743F, Other Flight Training (OFT), Project 675304, Aviation Resource Management Systems efforts transferred to PE
0804743F, OFT, Project 67A036, Air Resource Tool Enterprise Mission Information System (ARTEMIS) to ensure greater transparency.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Other Flight Training (OFT) program provides systems and data sources for recording and managing aircrew training information, aircrew/parachutist management,
flying hour tracking, flight pay management, and flying gate tracking for over 68,000 Air Force members to enhance safety-of-flight operations and to determine eligibility
to perform aviation related events.

 The OFT program includes the Aviation Resource Tool Enterprise Management Information System (ARTEMIS) effort, an on-line information system for base-level
 Deputy Commanders for Operations. ARTEMIS, which replaced the legacy Aviation Resource Management System (ARMS) that sunset in FY 2025, is a cloud-based
 system providing a common architecture to effectively support the implementation of Air Force flight management policies specified in AFI 11-401 and AFI 11-402. It
 ensures the accurate tracking of flying and ground training programs and delivers real-time analytics and operations management information for aircrew, missileer,
 and parachutist training and readiness. Covering over 68,000 aircrew/parachutists and used by 2,800 1C0X2 Career Field members with 2.2 million transactions per
 week, ARTEMIS provides operations managers with immediate visibility into flying program status, enabling effective resource allocation decisions and robust support
 for weapon systems requirements.

 Funding provides continuing developmental efforts that will focus on both the sustainment and continued development of ARTEMIS to enhance adoption and ensure
 Air Force readiness. Ongoing sustainment activities include minimizing system downtime, resolving escalated issues, maintaining security compliance, improving
 data quality and architecture for enterprise reporting, sustaining integrations with other Operations Enterprise Architecture (Ops EA) initiatives, and executing feature
 enhancements to improve the user experience. Concurrently, developmental efforts will provide additional flying operations information and interface this data into the
 Defense Readiness Reporting System Strategic (DRRS-S). These enhanced capabilities will be developed incrementally and include, but are not limited to, an electronic
 flight record, flying hour management, simulator and Remote Piloted Aircraft (RPA) management, a full career logbook, training look-back, aircrew member man-month
 allocation, enhanced resource and jump module management, and additional interfaces.



