 Space Systems Command's Space Force Portfolio Acquisition Executive for Infrastructure is developing the Digital Engineering Ecosystem (Project 645620) for
 Guardians across the Service Operational Function of Enterprise Networks. As a result, the Service will streamline capabilities development through institutional
 processes and advance technology associated with Golden Dome, ultimately providing a more resilient digital infrastructure to the USSF.

 Program Element 1203010SF, Space Force Information Technology (IT), Data Analytics, Digital Solutions, creates the foundation for the USSF's digital transformation,
 which will streamline acquisition, cybersecurity, life cycle management, and operations. This entails a distinct project, unified in their goal to fully exploit modern
 information technology:

 Project 645620, Digital Engineering, develops a computing environment to support the digital engineering needs of program offices across Space Systems Command
 (SSC), the product of which would serve programs throughout their life cycles. It also develops and prototypes Artificial Intelligence (AI) capabilities to be utilized to meet
 emerging needs.

 This program falls within the Multi-Mission mission area which provides the systems and efforts that evenly contribute to multiple mission areas across the space
 enterprise. Program interdependencies include: AFSCN Operations (1203130SF); Defensive Cyber Operations - Space (1203040SF); Enterprise Ground Services
 (1206770SF); Information Systems Security Program (1203140SF); Rapid Resilient Command and Control (1206772SF); Satellite Control Network (1203110SF); Space
 and Missile Test and Evaluation (1203173SF); and Space Defense Interface Network (1203904SF).

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver Space Force IT, Data Analytics, Digital Solutions
 capability. The use of such program funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 1206392SF and 1206398SF.



