Description: USSF DEE integrates across multiple security environments and authoritative sources of truth. This effort integrates
space models over varying maturity levels to function within the DEE to enable test components the ability to evaluate high-fidelity
modeling & simulations of real-world space assets capabilities and limitations to inform Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures
(TTPs) that need to be developed by readiness components.

FY 2026 Plans:
Supporting an enterprise DEE architecture. Begin down-selection and transition of discrete MVP efforts to an enterprise DEE
architecture. Mature MVP capabilities at multiple classification levels.

Integrating with USAF Joint Simulation Environment (JSE). Continue integration and leverage Operational Test, Training &
Integration (OTTI) capabilities to support readiness generation across space and Joint enterprise.

Leverage existing contract vehicles to enable DE and Integration for prototype infrastructure that allow for assessments and
capability solutions. Continue to prototype, develop, test and establish the Secure Facility, networks and systems, tools, and DEE
hosted on Hybrid cloud platform for cloud-computing and database storage.

Developing Special Access Program (SAP) capabilities and integrating critical security elements. Continue executing contracts
and funding for existing facilities, networks, accreditation, DEE, digital tools, MBSE, and modeling and analysis. Continue Special
Access Program (SAP) DEE development and sustainment to support Cyber operations, POM support planning, Kill Chain
analysis, digital source selection, enterprise integration, intelligence, and penetration testing.

Continuing critical security elements across all facilities, networks, DEE, systems, and tools. Security involves physical security,
information technology, and information assurance.

Delivering System Resiliency. Continue rapid response to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to
operate in the contested space domain. Activities may include, but are not limited to, program office support, studies, technical
analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership,
and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2027 Plans:
Supporting an enterprise DEE architecture. Continue to prototype, develop, test and establish the Secure Facility, networks and
systems, tools, and applications hosted on hybrid cloud platform for cloud-computing and database storage.



